The paper discusses coding schemes for random projections in the context of sub-linear time approximate near neighbor search, which is a problem commonly studied in computer science. The paper also mentions prior work on similarity estimation and training linear classifiers, which are topics related to computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information theory and coding, which suggests cs.IT (Information Theory) as a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper also discusses the task of near neighbor search, which is related to information retrieval, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another possible sub-category.
